<h2 class="header">Preview</h2>
<img style="border-radius:9px; max-width:414px;" src="https://img.appvalley.vip/screenshot/724.png" width="60%">
<h2 class="header">Description</h2>"In Intro to United States you<div class="desc" style="display: none;"> get to learn about the 50 states. Learning geography is necessary to become a good citizen of the world." - Geeks with Juniors <br />
<br />
Learn the names, shapes, location, and animals of each state through puzzles, challenges, and tracing exercises with this educational app for iPhone and iPad. <br />
<br />
Based on the proven methodology of Montessori.<br />
<br />
YOUR CHILD WILL LEARN: <br />
<br />
• To identify all 50 states in the United States <br />
• To discern the shapes of the states through a tracing activity<br />
• To recognize an animal from each state<br />
• The development of spatial relationships <br />
• Individual position in relationship to other states<br />
• Fine motor skills and vocabulary<br />
<br />
Intro to United States, from the creators of Intro to Math and Intro to Letters, includes the following activities in a universal app specially designed for the iPad and iPhone 6 and 6+: <br />
<br />
• NAMES OF THE STATES<br />
In a series of challenging activities, we learn the names of the states, finding their location on the map. <br />
<br />
• SHAPES, NAMES, AND PLACES <br />
Using the puzzle map, we work to develop name recognition, spatial relationship, and geographical location. <br />
<br />
• FULL MAP CHALLENGE<br />
Put your knowledge to the test, with a full scale, interactive puzzle map of the United States. <br />
<br />
• ANIMALS <br />
Tapping through the various animals of each state, we come to identify their unique characteristics with stunning illustrations by Alyssa Nassner.<br />
<br />
• MATCHING ANIMALS TO THEIR STATES <br />
In a series of engaging activities, we match the animals to their associated states, through this matching exercise.<br />
<br />
• SHAPES OF THE STATES<br />
Through an engaging, interactive tracing exercise, we focus on the shapes of the states.<br />
<br />
#learnthestates #youdidit<br />
